0101|- [HelpText]
0102|*Display-off mode of Survo
0104|*In certain applications of Survo it is good to freeze the main window
0105|*and display only selected portions of the work on the screen. This
0106|*is appropriate especially in sucros made as teaching programs or
0107|*as presentations of graphical displays.
0108|aThe key code PREFIX `L' `o' (in sucros {disp off}) disables the main window.
0109|*Text is written normally in the edit field but not shown in the window.
0110|*the main window is restored (and updated) by the keystrokes
0111|aPREFIX `L' `O' (in sucros {disp on}) or by the F8:EXIT key.
0113|*It is also possible to hide the main window by the WIN MIN command.
0114|*Then it is restored by WIN NORMAL.
0115|*Test this by continuous activation (F2 ESC) of the commands:
0116|*WIN MIN
0117|*WAIT 2
0118|*WIN NORMAL
0120|- shadow a: [LINK(q113_01.html)]
0121|*  S = More information on GPLOT specifications
S   |   a                                          |
